I think mark all comments as read should be available all the time either above the tree or in the main toolbar
{quote}

via Matt:
{quote}
where is the linked-review displayed? no where? should/could go near review objects content pane or near cookie trail
{quote}

via Matt:
{quote}
the user dropdown is limited to the top 10 matches, so you can never get a list of everyone, or even of everyone who as an A in their name
{quote}

via Matt:
{quote}
hitting down-arrow does not trigger the dropdown on edit reviewers, even if there is only a small list of allowed reviewers (eg 4 people).
{quote}

via Matt:
{quote}
hitting ENTER on an click-to-edit field (either title, or participant dropdowns) doesn't "submit". The only way to submit is to click-away.
{quote}

Ideally hitting ENTER should return the inline-edit field to it's pre-inline-editing state (i.e., without the input-box like border).

In contrast, tabbing away does do the 'submit' but, by neccessity, focuses the next field.

via Matt:
{quote}
in a draft review in the FishEye project. Hit Edit Review. Clicking Done closes the dialog. Hit Edit REview again. Change the project to Clover. Hit Done. The Edit Review dialog comes back up after submit, instead of staying on the main review page.
{quote}

In the _Edit Details_ dialog (via Matt):

{quote}
no indicator that user-dropdowns are completeable... When I click on "moderator" field, I get a text area only. Would be nice if there was a down-triangle hint that this was more than an auto-complete (down-triangle, or little search magnifying glass)
{quote}

As noticed by all in the blitz, there were no review updated notices nor did avatars update with their completion.

